<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="L" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Liver1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Liver,</orth> 1) one who lives, a man: <cit><quote>there's --s out of Britain,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 3.4.143" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 4, 143</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) one living in a particular manner: <cit><quote>humble --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 2.3.20" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 II, 3, 20</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the longer l. take all,</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 1.5.17" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 5, 17</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>prouder --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 3.3.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 3, 9</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>